Description¶

This is a countrywide car accident dataset, which covers 49 states of the USA. The accident data are collected from February 2016 to Dec 2021, using multiple APIs that provide streaming traffic incident (or event) data. These APIs broadcast traffic data captured by a variety of entities, such as the US and state departments of transportation, law enforcement agencies, traffic cameras, and traffic sensors within the road-networks. Currently, there are about 2.8 million accident records in this dataset. Check here to learn more about this dataset.¶

Data Wrangling¶

Downloading the data from kaggle directly to aviod downloading the data to your local machine due to the large data size(1.5 GB).¶

pip install opendatasets --upgrade --quiet

Note: you may need to restart the kernel to use updated packages.

od.download(download_url)

Q10: What is the trend of accidents over the years?

In [44]:
# The dataset contains years from 2016 to 2021
df_2016 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2016].value_counts().sum()
df_2017 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2017].value_counts().sum()
df_2018 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2018].value_counts().sum()
df_2019 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2019].value_counts().sum()
df_2020 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2020].value_counts().sum()
df_2021 = df[df.Start_Time.dt.year == 2021].value_counts().sum()
In [45]:
trend_of_accidents = [df_2016,df_2017,df_2018,df_2019,df_2020,df_2021]
years = [2016,2017,2018,2019,2020,2021]
In [46]:
plt.plot(trend_of_accidents,years,'o-g', linewidth=4)

plt.title('Trend of Accidents over the years',fontdict={'fontsize':14})

There's positive trend of accidents over the years which means that the US accidents count increases every year.¶

Summary¶

Limitations:¶

  • There are many missing values in multiple columns with high percentages.
  • Also, The data is collected from FEB of 2016, so data of January is missing which reduicng the number of accidents in the winter season.
  • New York City which has the highest population not included in the datset.

These downfalls may affect the answers to some questions. Also, due to the large size of the data set its benfitual to drop some columns as to make it easier to deal with the data set on your local machine.¶

This analysis helps to point out the necessatiy of trying to figure out a solution to the problem of the increasing number of accidents in the US as the trend of the number of accidents seems to be increasing over time by hundreds of thousands of accidents.¶
